237	  Let $C$ be a scheme over $\Spec k$ and $\mathcal U$ an indexed family of opens of $C$. Define the \v{C}ech cochain complex of the structure sheaf with respect to $\mathcal U$ to be the standard \v{C}ech complex applied to the underlying presheaf of the $k$-module-valued structure sheaf. This is a cochain complex valued in $k$-modules, indexed by $\mathbb N$.
238	\end{definition}
