612	\section{\v{C}ech-side acyclicity carrier}
613	\label{sec:moduleK_cech_acyclic_cover}
614	
615	We introduce a carrier predicate capturing positive-degree vanishing of \v{C}ech cohomology, together with a consumer that transports this vanishing to derived cohomology once a comparison isomorphism is available.
616	
617	\begin{definition}\leanok
618	[\v{C}ech acyclicity carrier predicate]
619	  \label{def:Scheme_IsCechAcyclicCover}
620	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.Scheme.IsCechAcyclicCover}
621	  \uses{def:Scheme_cechCohomology}
